==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brandenburg
<hw>Bran"den*burg</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
<etsep>Brandenburg</etsep>, a province and a town of Prussia.]</ety>
<def>A kind of decoration for the breast of a coat, sometimes only a
frog with a loop, but in some military uniforms enlarged into a broad
horizontal stripe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He wore a coat . . . trimmed with <qex>Brandenburgs</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Smollett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brander</ent>⟦br⟧
